article.headline: St. John's 77, Bethune-Cookman 59
article.story: NEW YORK -- Sean Evans scored 18 points to lead St. John's to its sixth straight victory, 77-59 over Bethune-Cookman on Sunday. D.J. Kennedy added 15 points, Paris Horne had 11 and Malik Boothe 10 for the Red Storm (8-1), whose winning streak has all been at Carnesecca Arena. C.J. Reed had 15 points for the Wildcats (4-5), who had won three straight. Jarrell Thomas added 13 points and Kene Anusionwu had 11 for Bethune-Cookman. Reed had five points in the Wildcats' 8-0 run that gave them a 12-9 lead. Horne hit a 3-pointer that keyed the Red Storm's 10-0 run that made it 19-12 and gave them the lead for good. Horne had two 3s and Evans hit two jumpers in St. John's 17-2 run that opened the second half and put it ahead 52-30 with 15:01 to play. It was the first meeting between the schools.
